{
  "text": "The low incidence of late CMV infection observed in the standard-risk group is also reported in two others studies. In one, the authors did not observe primary late-onset CMV viremia after 100 days of pre-emptive therapy, but recurrence occurred in 4% (1 of 13 patients) of D+/R+ but in none of nine D-/R+ patients [CITATION_1] . In another study, asymptomatic CMV infection rate was 48% after six months; it only increased to 49% after 12 months [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
